<DOC><DOCNO> AP890519-0240 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-19-89 1309EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-AccountingMerger-List     05-19 0286</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Accounting Merger-List,0306</SECOND><HEAD>Fifteen Biggest Accounting Firms</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Accounting Merger Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here is a list of the 15 biggest accountingfirms on the basis of their 1988 revenue from U.S. operations,compiled by Bowman's Accounting Report of Atlanta.   Included are each firm's U.S. partners, U.S. revenue andinternational revenue.   1. Arthur Andersen, 1,227 U.S. partners, $1.71 billion U.S.revenue, $2.82 billion international revenue.   2. KPMG (Peat Marwick), 1,933 U.S. partners, $1.64 billion U.S.revenue, $3.90 billion international revenue.   3. Ernst andamp; Whinney, 1,280 U.S. partners, $1.17 billion U.S.revenue, $2.19 billion international revenue.   4. Coopers andamp; Lybrand, 1,270 U.S. partners, $1.14 billion U.S.revenue (estimate), $2.50 billion international revenue (estimate).   5. Price Waterhouse, 870 U.S. partners, $960 million U.S.revenue, $2.20 billion international revenue.   6. Arthur Young, 889 U.S. partners, $843 million U.S. revenue,$2.05 billion international revenue.   7. Deloitte Haskins andamp; Sells, 853 U.S. partners, $820 millionU.S. revenue, $1.92 billion international revenue.   8. Touche Ross, 774 U.S. partners, $796 million U.S. revenue,$1.84 billion international revenue.   9. Laventhol andamp; Horwath, 460 U.S. partners, $306 million U.S.revenue, $556 million international revenue.   10. Grant Thorton, 341 U.S. partners, $200 million U.S. revenue,$721 million international revenue.   11. BDO Seidman, 316 U.S. partners, $157 million U.S. revenue,$758 million international revenue.   12. McGladrey andamp; Pullen, 380 U.S. partners, $139 million U.S.revenue, $402 million international revenue.   13. Kenneth Leventhal, 61 U.S. partners, $126 million U.S.revenue, $292 million international revenue.   14. Pannell Kerr Forster, 125 U.S. partners, $87 million U.S.revenue, $317 million international revenue.   15. Spicer andamp; Oppenheim, 97 U.S. partners, $70 million U.S.revenue, $344 million international revenue.</TEXT><TEXT>   Note: Figures are for fiscal year 1988, not calendar year.</TEXT></DOC>